e.g. Currently, Clover reports the following method as fully covered, even if (getA() == null) is never false.

{code}
 public boolean isBlah() {
        return getA() == null || getB() == null;
}
{code}

These variables need to be namespaced somehow by Clover to prevent clashes with local variables etc...
e.g. the following method,
{code}
  @Test(dataProvider = "test1")
  public void verifyNames(Object p) {
    // do nothing
  }
{code}

fails with this javac error:
{code}
p is already defined in verifyNames(java.lang.Object)
{code}

for [clover-merge Ant task|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CLOVER/clover-merge], new parameters for the outer element (the fist parameter section on the page):

| update | if set to {{true}} and there is an existing database at {{initString}}, that database will be included in the merge | No. Defaults to {{false}} |
| updateSpan | if {{update}} is {{true}}, this span is used when merging any existing database at {{initString}} | No. Defaults to 0 seconds. |


for the [CloverMerge CLI|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CLOVER/CloverMerge], the same new options - please put as first in the options table:

| \-u, \--update [interval] | if specified, any existing database specified by \-i will be included in the merge. If interval is specified, it is used as the span when reading the existing database. |

The current log message reads:
{code}  [junit] Clover estimates saving around 39 seconds on this optimized test run. {code}

This could be more informative if it said:
{code} [junit] Clover estimates saving around 39 seconds on this optimized test run. Total test run time aprox. 5 minutes. {code}

{quote}
I'd like to create a custom "To Do" Test Results column where tests which are not yet implemented could be summed. This way I will be displaying tests passing, failing and "To Do".

My "not implemented" tests throw a junit.framework.Assert.fail("not implemented"). Is there some way to configure a Clover column to read this message and add to the count of "To Do" tests?
{quote}

Issue reported: https://support.atlassian.com/browse/CLV-5127

This is a webapp, with two .war files deployed to jetty.
It is in clover-ant/testcases/projects/webapp.

for maven, test using:
{code}
$mvn clean test.
{code}
